data.title: MAIJA DIGORGIO — EMANCIPATED TALENT MANAGEMENT
data.text:
MAIJA DIGORGIO

Comedian/Actor/Writer/Radio Personality/Filmmaker/Musician

In her first year doing stand up, Maija took the comedy world by storm taping five national TV appearances, receiving a standing ovation at NBC’s Live from the Apollo, and performing at the HBO Aspen Comedy Festival.

Maija has taken her talents to countless prestigious venues worldwide—including the Beacon Theater, the New Orleans’ Essence Festival, and Scotland’s Edinburgh Festival. Her TV performances include HBO’s Def Comedy Jam, NBC’s Comics Unleashed, Live at Gotham, Fox’s Laughs, Uncontrolled Comedy Hour, Bet’s Comic View, and Showtime’s Michael Vick Comedy Explosion. She has had the opportunity to perform alongside the likes of Dave Chappelle, Kevin Hart, Bill Burr, Dane Cook, Wanda Sykes, Mike Epps, and Tracy Morgan.

In her comedy, Maija examines the complexities of what it means to be a mixed race, multicultural woman through the context of trivial topics like dating, family, and daily observations.

She’s directed the film “Bitter Jester”, receiving rave reviews from Variety and The New York Times. She’s also established herself as a radio personality co-hosting Hot 97’s “The Morning Show with Ed and Maija”.
